The three people suspected of kidnapping Amy'Leigh de Jager are set to appear in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrates Court this morning. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Three people arrested in connection with the kidnapping of Amy'Leigh de Jager appeared in the Vanderbijlpark Magistrates Court on Monday. READ: Three arrested for Amy'Leigh kidnapping The six-year-old was taken from her school last week, but then released. The news that one of the alleged kidnappers was a teacher at the school, and a close family friend, came as a shock to many residents of the Vaal town. After initially demanding R2-million as ransom, her kidnappers abandoned their plan. At the appearance, the matter was postponed to 19 September for a formal bail application.